snippet.textDisplay:
Seems like the Benz is the new evo for the upper-class kids, lol.

Thought you would save a ton of money if you would just buy a used evo in modified it. I mean for us regular people that don't feel like spending 60k on a nicer interior, evo/sti/focus rs.

To be fair you should have tried to drift with the Mercedes in regular mode. The Golf R and RS3 don't have drift mode. We need to see how much it plows or a doesn't plow without drift mode.

The benz's definitely impressive. But if you were to modify the benz and rs3 I think you could probably get more power on Pump Fuel on the RS3... And cheaper. Also the RS3 needs exhaust sound good.

Renntech, is making a 592hp package for the benz. I'm sure it will cost an arm and a leg but nothing that's too good for junior. After all I remember seeing evos at the shop with 30 to $40,000 dropped in them back in the day, given to kids. The only thing is it didn't say what fuel it makes that power on. I'd love to see what they can Max it out on pump gas.
